Description:
   Road Sweep is a low-angled combat technique developed by Wardens who
   train on uneven terrain. The warrior delivers a sweeping kick or strike
   targeting the opponent's lower body — knees, shins, or ankles. The
   blow trips or staggers the target, potentially knocking them off balance
   and interrupting their next action.

   Road Sweep is an early offensive skill that complements the Warden's
   direct assault style. It deals physical damage and can interrupt the
   target's positioning, making follow-up strikes easier to land. The
   technique is most effective against opponents who rely on footwork and
   mobility, as disrupting their stance negates much of their defensive
   advantage.
